member.param:
The skeleton of the generated method where a  should be placed
anywhere that needs to have some indenting,  anywhere that
needs some initial indenting.
It should look something like:
 public void MethodName()
 {
 throw new NotImplementedException();
 }

remarks.para:
 For example, given the following Razor file:
 
 <div>
     @if (true)
     {
         // Some code
     }
 </div>

 @code {
     private string Name { get; set; }
 }

 The generator will go through that syntax tree and produce the following C# document:
 
 // <div>
     @if (true)
     {
         // Some code
     }
 // </div>

 class F
 {
     private string Name { get; set; }
 }
